rules: Rule1: If event1 is scheduled, then whenever program1 is not funded, employee1 has not passed assessment1.
Rule2: Provided that event2 is scheduled, event2 is confirmed.
Rule3: Assuming event2 is scheduled, event2 is recorded.
Rule4: If event2 is scheduled, then it is not the case that event2 is virtual.
Rule5: Either event2 is scheduled or event1 is scheduled.
Rule6: If event2 is confirmed, then event2 is cancelled.
Rule7: Provided that event2 is confirmed, it is not the case that event2 is cancelled.
Rule8: If trainer2 is qualified, then whenever trainer1 is qualified, provided that program1 is not funded, trainer1 is certified.
Rule9: Assuming trainer1 is approved, trainer2 is qualified.
Rule10: Either employee1 is registered or employee2 has not completed course1.
Rule11: Employee1 is a manager or employee1 is a supervisor.

Rule12: If employee1 is a supervisor, then whenever it is not the case that if employee1 is enrolled in program1 then employee2 has not completed course1, and employee1 does not have a conflict, conflict1 is resolved.

Rule13: Either employee1 is a director or if employee1 is a manager, then provided that it is not the case that if employee1 is enrolled in program1 then employee2 has not completed course1, and employee1 does not have a conflict, conflict1 is resolved.
Rule14: If skill1 is required, then assuming facility1 is available, facility1 is booked.
Rule15: Either skill1 is basic or it is not the case that skill1 is mandatory.
Rule16: Skill1 is advanced or facility1 is not available.
Rule17: Provided that employee1 is a beginner, skill1 is not advanced.
Rule18: Employee1 is a beginner or employee1 is intermediate.
Rule19: If employee1 is intermediate, then skill1 is not advanced.
Rule20: Assuming event1 is remote, event2 is not in-person.
Rule21: If event2 is onsite, then event2 is not scheduled.
Rule22: Provided that event2 is in the morning, event2 is onsite.
Rule23: Either event2 is in the morning or event2 is in the afternoon.
Rule24: If event2 is in the afternoon, then event2 is onsite.
Rule25: Whenever event1 is recurring, event1 is scheduled.
Rule26: Provided that event1 is monthly, event1 is weekly.
Rule27: If event2 is live, then whenever event2 is scheduled, event2 is not recorded.
Rule28: Either event2 is live or event2 is interactive.
Rule29: Assuming event2 is interactive, then if event2 is scheduled, event2 is not recorded.
Rule30: If employee1 is enrolled in program1, then employee1 is enrolled in workshop1.
Rule31: If employee1 is enrolled in workshop1, then employee2 has not completed course1.
Rule32: Either facility1 is available or program1 is funded.
Rule33: Facility2 is available or if facility1 is available, then facility1 is booked.
Rule34: If it is not the case that if event2 is scheduled then event2 is virtual, then event2 is in-person.
Rule35: Provided that it is not the case that either employee2 is registered or employee1 is not registered, employee1 is waitlisted.

Rule36: If it is not the case that either employee1 is delegated task1 or if employee2 is assigned to project1, then provided that employee1 is assigned to project1, employee1 has completed course1, then employee2 is delegated task1.

Rule37: Assuming it is not the case that either employee1 is delegated task1 or if employee2 is assigned to project1, then provided that employee1 is assigned to project1, employee1 has completed course1, then it is not the case that employee2 is delegated task1.
Rule38: If it is not the case that if employee1 is enrolled in program1 then employee2 has not completed course1, then employee1 has a conflict.

Rule39: If it is not the case that if it is not the case that if employee1 is enrolled in program1 then employee2 has not completed course1, then employee1 does not have a conflict, then it is not the case that conflict1 is resolved.
Rule40: Provided that it is not the case that if skill1 is not required then skill1 is optional, skill1 is mandatory.
Rule41: If it is not the case that if event1 is not recurring then event1 is monthly, then event1 is quarterly.
Rule42: Assuming it is not the case that if program1 is not funded then trainer1 is certified, trainer2 is certified.
Rule43: Provided that it is not the case that if program1 is not funded then employee1 has completed course1, employee2 has completed course1.
Rule44: Provided that event1 is not recurring, event1 is not weekly.
Rule45: Assuming program1 is not funded, employee1 has passed assessment1.
Rule46: Provided that program1 is not funded, employee1 is assigned to project1.
Rule47: Whenever program1 is not funded, trainer1 is not certified.
Rule48: Provided that program1 is not funded, employee1 has not completed course1.
